name: Org
description: Use the Cache.Org class to add, retrieve, and manage values in the org cache. Unlike the session cache, the org cache is not tied to any session and is available to the organization across requests and to all users.

contains(string).name: contains
contains(string).overrideSignature: public static override Boolean contains(String key)
contains(string).description: Returns true if the org cache contains a cached value corresponding to the specified key.

key.name: key
key.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage.

contains(set<string>).name: contains
contains(set<string>).overrideSignature: public static override List<Boolean> contains(Set<String> keys)
contains(set<string>).description: Returns true if the org cache contains the specified key entries.

keys.name: keys
keys.description: A set of keys that uniquely identifies cached values. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage.

get(string).name: get
get(string).overrideSignature: public static override Object get(String key)
get(string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the org cache.

key.name: key
key.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage.

get(system.type,string).name: get
get(system.type,string).signature: public static Object get(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
get(system.type,string).overrideSignature: public static override Object get(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
get(system.type,string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the org cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

key.name: key
key.description: The Apex class that implements the CacheBuilder interface. A case-sensitive string value that, combined with the class name corresponding to the cacheBuilder parameter, uniquely identifies a cached value.

getavggettime().name: getAvgGetTime
getavggettime().description: Returns the average time taken to get a key from the org cache, in nanoseconds.

getavgvaluesize().name: getAvgValueSize
getavgvaluesize().description: Returns the average item size for keys in the org cache, in bytes.

getcapacity().name: getCapacity
getcapacity().description: Returns the percentage of org cache capacity that has been used.

getkeys().name: getKeys
getkeys().description: Returns a set of all keys that are stored in the org cache and visible to the invoking namespace.

getmaxgettime().name: getMaxGetTime
getmaxgettime().description: Returns the maximum time taken to get a key from the org cache, in nanoseconds.

getmaxvaluesize().name: getMaxValueSize
getmaxvaluesize().description: Returns the maximum item size for keys in the org cache, in bytes.

getmissrate().name: getMissRate
getmissrate().description: Returns the miss rate in the org cache.

getname().name: getName
getname().description: Returns the name of the default cache partition.

getnumkeys().name: getNumKeys
getnumkeys().description: Returns the total number of keys in the org cache.

getpartition(string).name: getPartition
getpartition(string).overrideSignature: public static override cache.OrgPartition getPartition(String partitionName)
getpartition(string).description: Returns a partition from the org cache that corresponds to the specified partition name.

partitionname.name: partitionName
partitionname.description: A partition name that is qualified by the namespace, for example, namespace.partition.

put(string,object).name: put
put(string,object).signature: public static void put(String key, Object value)
put(string,object).overrideSignature: public static override void put(String key, Object value)
put(string,object).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the org cache. The put method can write only to the cache in your orgs namespace.

value.name: value
value.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable.

put(string,object,cache.visibility).name: put
put(string,object,cache.visibility).signature: public static void put(String key, Object value, Cache.Visibility visibility)
put(string,object,cache.visibility).overrideSignature: public static override void put(String key, Object value, Cache.Visibility visibility)
put(string,object,cache.visibility).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the org cache and sets the cached values visibility.

visibility.name: visibility
visibility.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable. Indicates whether the cached value is available only to Apex code that is executing in the same namespace or to Apex code executing from any namespace.

put(string,object,integer).name: put
put(string,object,integer).signature: public static void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs)
put(string,object,integer).overrideSignature: public static override void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs)
put(string,object,integer).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the org cache and sets the cached values lifetime.

ttlsecs.name: ttlSecs
ttlsecs.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable. The amount of time, in seconds, to keep the cached value in the org cache. The maximum is 172,800 seconds (48 hours). The minimum value is 300 seconds or 5 minutes. The default value is 86,400 seconds (24 hours).

put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.name: put
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.signature: public static void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs, cache.Visibility visibility, Boolean immutable)
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.overrideSignature: public static override void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs, cache.Visibility visibility, Boolean immutable)
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the org cache. This method also sets the cached values lifetime, visibility, and whether it can be overwritten by another namespace.

immutable.name: immutable
immutable.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable. The amount of time, in seconds, to keep the cached value in the org cache. The maximum is 172,800 seconds (48 hours). The minimum value is 300 seconds or 5 minutes. The default value is 86,400 seconds (24 hours). Indicates whether the cached value is available only to Apex code that is executing in the same namespace or to Apex code executing from any namespace. Indicates whether the cached value can be overwritten by another namespace (false) or not (true).

remove(string).overrideSignature: public static override Boolean remove(String key)
remove(string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the org cache.

key.name: key
key.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. For information about the format of the key name, see Usage.

remove(system.type,string).signature: public static Boolean remove(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
remove(system.type,string).overrideSignature: public static override Boolean remove(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
remove(system.type,string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the org cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

key.description: The Apex class that implements the CacheBuilder interface. A case-sensitive string value that, combined with the class name corresponding to the cacheBuilder parameter, uniquely identifies a cached value.
